The paper presents a method to quantify and diagnose knowledge representations of pre-trained deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on measuring input information of a specific layer from two perspectives using entropy-based metrics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most likely category. The paper also deals with deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed metrics in analyzing existing deep-learning techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
